items.title: Here's what major Wall Street banks are telling clients to do about the shutdown
items.description: Wall Street banks largely told clients to expect a typical short shutdown and bet on a comeback in stocks if there's any major weakness.

items.title: Barclays downgrades AT&T to equal weight, says upside is limited after recent gains
items.description: AT&T has outperformed this year, climbing 24%, but is likely to face a more challenging environment ahead, the bank said.

items.title: Carvana gets an upgrade from Jefferies, which says momentum for car retailer is picking up
items.description: Shares of the online car retailer have already outperformed this year, up more than 85%. Jefferies expects there's further upside.

items.description: Here are Wednesday's biggest calls on Wall Street.

items.title: The stock market usually doesn't care about government shutdowns. This time may not follow the script
items.description: The current funding dispute is raising concern among investors and strategists, who say the economic backdrop now is the weakest since 1990.
